s in standardized space (`StandardScaler` fit once on the shared negative pool, reused for both CAVs). Per layer the cosine is the **mean across `avg` and `max` pooling** (`CAV_POOLINGS`), matching the RQ3 / backbone figures. Set `CAV_POOLINGS = ['avg']` for GAP-only.\n- **VLM judge:** `Qwen2-VL-2B-Instruct`, logit-based `P(yes)`, threshold 0.25 (exp 1.1).\n- **Negatives:** `negative_kind='full'` (full-scene VTCAV `/random`), as in the thesis.\n- **Reference labelling:** for `wood`, `water`, `bubbly` the reference set is the **T2I (synthetic)** dataset, not DTD — figures/tables here call it *reference baseline*, not *manual (DTD)*.\n\n> Run top-to-bottom on Kaggle/Colab with the extracted crops, DTD/T2I reference sets, prompt-variation crops and the negative pool attached. The VLM judge dominates runtime — keep the `max_*` caps modest for a smoke run.","metadata":{}},{"id":"e9732b77-f806-4fdf-a98f-95c4da74b4a7","cell_type":"code","source":"# ─── Dependencies ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n!pip install -q open_clip_torch \"transformers>=4.45\" accelerate matplotlib \"seaborn>=0.13\" scikit-learn pandas tqdm","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-30T10:29:19.980919Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-30T10:29:19.981205Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-30T10:29:27.892176Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-30T10:29:19.981183Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-30T10:29:27.891108Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m1.5/1.5 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m24.9 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0ma \u001b[36m0:00:01\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m12.2/12.2 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m95.1 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m:00:01\u001b[0m0:01\u001b[0m\n\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m44.8/44.8 kB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m2.9